    "Body": " Posted by: Tomika Sanders, MA Tomika Sanders, MA Talent Acquisition Lead/Manager, Senior HR Professional Role Summary: The Director of Investment Operations Technology leads the technology for investment operations, fund administration, financial reporting, tax and post trade lifecycle capabilities for the firm. We are undertaking a significant transformation of our Investments technology capabilities, and this person will be a key leader supporting this transformation journey! We have multiple, intricate sets of systems supporting investment operations, middle office and fund administration and have built and embedded custom IP within them over the years. These systems help us maintain a competitive advantage. We need to retrain and enhance them while modernizing our technology estate! This is a key leadership role, responsible for inspiring and leading technology teams and working with key business partners. They will lead technology efforts in alignment with the firm\u2019s strategy. Specific areas of importance include automated reconciliations maximizing AI/ML capabilities, centralized management of sophisticated workflows, driving towards 100% automated straight thru processing. The Director of Investment Operations Technology will drive enterprise design and development. They will focus on digital transformation using AI, ML and Blockchain; data engineering and data analytics. What you will do: Create a roadmap for modernization of investment operations technology in the firm, using current technologies and design patterns. Modernize the deployment of microservices-based architecture, cloud technologies, artificial intelligence and machine learning technologies. Provide inspirational leadership and management to build strong application development teams. Provide technology leadership and advice to business partners on architecture, capabilities, projects, opportunities and problems. Participate in enterprise prioritization process to represent the business needs and gain consensus for allocation of resources to complete the work. Offer thought leadership to the firm by fostering standard methodologies, owning the organization vision, reference architecture and in strategy formulation etc. Lead technology delivery, plan and lead staffing requirements, scheduling and projects in an agile environment. Review performance, quality, budget, organization and standards of the development team efforts. Participate on the Application Development leadership team. Influence strategic direction and architecture for the Application Development organization and ensure all tactics are in support of the long-term strategy. Improve the efficiency, cost-effectiveness and quality of the Information Technology department and business area. Ensure accountability of management of security, compliance and audit requirements for all systems, including information security related projects or requests. Required Skills/Experience: Bachelor\u2019s degree preferably in Computer Science, MBA is an added plus 15+ years of experience with significant leadership and supervisory tenure, preferably in buy side firms. Experience in building and deploying operational systems to support a portfolio\u2019s lifecycle. Experience with leading Fund Administration systems, Middle Office systems, Tax and reporting systems, like SimCorp, Eagle, FIS, Omgeo etc. will be helpful. A strong expertise in Investment Operations architectures including trade lifecycle, custody operations, cash management, corporate actions, vendor oversight and investment data. Significant experience operating in financial services, with preference for buy-side (asset management, investment manager, hedge fund, mutual fund) experience. Working understanding of the entire value chain of investment management including research, portfolio construction, portfolio management, risk management, investments analytics etc. Cross asset class knowledge \u2013Equities, Fixed Income, Alternatives and Multi-Asset flows. Outstanding interpersonal skills including the ability to interact with individuals at all levels of the organization in both verbal and written form. Solid technical knowledge including expertise in Cloud platforms (AWS preferred), microservices architecture, enterprise integration design patterns, and current data engineering practices. Solid understanding of artificial intelligence and machine learning with applicability in financial services is a big plus. Inspirational people leader, who can serve as a role model, to build and lead an Information Technology team. Strong enterprise level project management and vendor relationship skills. "
